'''Thomas J. Spanos''' (SL 1876) is the Legion Membership Officer of the real-world [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]] costuming organization. His likeness, as drawn by ''Star Wars'' artist and author [[Jan Duursema]], appears in many issues of the ''[[Star Wars: Legacy]]'' comics, particularly [[Legacy (2006) 6|''Legacy'' (2006) 6]] as Imperial Knight [[Ganner Krieg]].<ref name="characterbasis">{{WebCite|url=http://www.paralada.org/Estonia_self/Estonia_htm/SWgeekhtm/IK_Ganner_Krieg/index.htm|text=Imperial Knight Ganner Krieg, model and costume|archivedate=20080130082156}}</ref><ref name="JCF">{{JCFCite|url=posts/30459895|board=Authors and Artists|thread=The Official Jan Duursema Discussion Thread|user=[[Jan Duursema|Jan_Duursema]]|date=2009-09-29|time=6:22 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160521115027/http://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-official-jan-duursema-discussion-thread.5915607/page-94}}</ref>

In ''Star Wars: Legacy'', Jan Duursema's depiction of [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]] was in fact based on a partially completed costume of Spanos'.<ref name="JCF" /><ref name="fancostume">{{WebCite|url=http://www.paralada.org/Estonia_self/Estonia_htm/SWgeekhtm/Dxun/DarthBaneCC.htm|text=Darth Bane, post Dxun costume|archivedate=20071012230614}}</ref>

[[Joe Corroney]] has based several of his drawings on Spanos' costumes. An image of [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine's]] [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] in the [[Star Wars Insider 83|''Star Wars Insider'' 83]] article, ''[[20 Most Memorable Moments of the Expanded Universe]]'', is based on Spanos' work.<ref name="Palpatinecostume">{{WebCite|url=http://www.paralada.org/Estonia_self/Estonia_htm/SWgeekhtm/cEAA.html|text=Curriculum Vitate of the Clone Emperor|archivedate=20031014112756}}</ref> Spanos' costume of [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]] was also referenced by Corroney in the [[Star Wars Insider 89|''Star Wars Insider'' 89]] article "[[Underworld: A Galaxy of Scum and Villainy]]."<ref name="Xizorcostume">{{WebCite|url=http://www.paralada.org/Estonia_self/Estonia_htm/SWgeekhtm/Xizor_htm/XizorAA.html|text=Curriculum Vitae of Prince Xizor|archivedate=20040306131846}}</ref>

